1. Basic Structure Tags
<!DOCTYPE html> → tells browser it's HTML5
<html> → root element
<head> → metadata (not visible)
<title> → page title (tab name)
<body> → visible content

2. Text & Content Tags
<h1> → main heading (SEO important)
<p> → paragraph
<br> → line break
<hr> → horizontal line

3. Formatting Tags
<b> → just bold
<strong> → important (SEO)
<i> → italic
<em> → emphasis (semantic)
<mark> mark the text
<small>make text smaller
<del>create a deleted text
<ins>inserted text
<sub>subscript
<sup>superscript

4. Links & Media
<a> → hyperlink
<img> → image
<video> → video
<audio> → sound

5. List Tags
<ul> → unordered list
<ol> → ordered list
<li> → list item
<dl> → description list

6. Layout / Structure Tags (VERY IMPORTANT)
<div> → block container
<span> → inline container
<header> → top section
<footer> → bottom
<section> → grouped content
<article> → independent content
<nav> → navigation bar
<aside> → sidebar
<main> → main content

7. Form Tags
<form> → form container
<input> → user input
<textarea> → multi-line input
<select> → dropdown
<button> → action
<option> → dropdown option
<label> → form label

8. Table Tags
<table> → table
<tr> → row
<td> → data
<th> → heading
<thead> → table header
<tbody> → table body
<tfoot> → table footer

9. Meta & Head Tags
<meta> → SEO, charset
<link> → CSS file
<script>  JavaScript
<style> internal